# **Google Scrape extension install manual**

1. ### Download. 

   First we need to download the archive with Google Scrape to your PC or MAC.

[https://drive.google.com/file/d/1sjgLfMQVI907M3XnzYJYWJGLTn8YMe3w/](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1sjgLfMQVI907M3XnzYJYWJGLTn8YMe3w/)

New versions of the extensions available for download in our Discord channel \#test-app:  
[https://discord.com/channels/732698343951695963/1197447020839976990](https://discord.com/channels/732698343951695963/1197447020839976990)

2. Extract the archive (right button on it / Extract here). For better use you can relocate it in the RemoteHelpers folder on your computer, because if you delete the folder with extension it will be broken).

3. ### Instalation. 

   Then open Google Chrome, open Chrome menu on the right top corner ![][image1],   
   Extensions / Manage Extensions ![][image2]  
4. Next we need to turn on Developer mode on the right top corner ![][image3]  
5. After that on left top corner press button Load unpacked ![][image4]  
6. Find and select folder of extracted archive and press Select folder  
   ![][image5]  
7. If you doing right, you will see loaded extension:  
     
     
     
     
8. Next step to pin extension for better using, top menu and Pin button

   

   

   

   

   

   

9. ### Sign in. 

   Press Google Scrape extension button ![][image6], insert your personal email and password of the CRM and press Sign in button:  
   ![][image7]

10. ### Using. 

    Fill of the fields of you Google search request, for example:  
    ![][image8]  
11. Click Search and wait for a minute without any clicking.

12. ### Results in Discord. 

    Then you will see results in the Discord channel \#google-extension-unique-lead

[https://discord.com/channels/732698343951695963/1245715744130334772](https://discord.com/channels/732698343951695963/1245715744130334772)

13. To see only your results, you can do search by your name on the right top corner:![][image9] Put here your first and second name and press Enter.  
    (if you did the next search, you should run the search again. Note: on the bottom of this menu you will see the last search request and you don’t need to always do new).

14. ### Results in Chrome.

    Also you will see a newly created page with unique companies ![][image10]   
    ![][image11]  
    Blue links are not clicked yet companies, red links are already clicked.  
15. Important to check the company location in the headline or About page. Sometimes from google results you will see companies not from the country, what you need to find.  
16. After you checked all page results, change to the next page and click Search ![][image12]  
    The same for the next pages. The last search inserted information will be saved in the extension fields.  
17. If you got the end of a search, you will see this:  
      
      
      
      
      
      
  


18. ### Next search request.

    Change city or industry, click ![][image13] to start from the first page and click Search.  
      
19. Don’t do a second search, if you haven’t checked all the links from the first search page. Next search will delete the first search page and create a new one with the same name.

### Dark or light theme.

 If your system settings use a Light theme, the appearance of the extension will be Light, if a dark theme \- the extension will be in a dark theme.

## Search extension table

After creating the first search you should fill this information in the table. It’s for analyzing of the work.

1. Open the link:

[https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1v-caMlLDYgAKJyPzYksi9rst9onV1VZtrmpOF\_BHPi0/](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1v-caMlLDYgAKJyPzYksi9rst9onV1VZtrmpOF_BHPi0/)

2. Fill all the fields of your Google request.  
   ![][image14]  
- **Query**. Copy and paste here the full query of your Google search like on the screen above.  
- **Manager**. Choose from the dropdown menu your name.  
- **Date**. Doble click in the cell and choose today’s date.  
- **Country**. Select the country you are workin on.  
- **City**. Input current city.  
- **Industry**. Paste here the industry of the request.  
- **Size**. Choose from the dropdown menu your size of the companies.

Here is example, how it should look like:

![][image15]

3. If you change city, industry or size of the company, you should go to the fee row and fill all the fields again with a new Google request.
